/gradlew text eol=lf
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.jar binary

# Source files must stay LF in the working tree on every platform so the Linux
# Docker build (and Spotless inside it) does not see CRLF drift from Windows
# checkouts. Without these rules, a Windows clone with core.autocrlf=true
# converts the working-tree copy to CRLF and the resulting `docker compose
# build` either fails (Spotless) or burns a re-format diff round-trip.
*.java text eol=lf
*.kt text eol=lf
*.kts text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.properties text eol=lf
*.html text eol=lf
*.css text eol=lf
*.js text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.xml text eol=lf
*.sql text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
Dockerfile text eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf
